commit_list.message:
Reshuffling resources to make reports independent and added metrics.

* Reports are no longer dependent on a Server. This allows a Report to
  span multiple servers if desired
* Metrics have been separated out into their own AR model so that they
  can be associated with both a Server and a Report. Again, this allows
  for metrics on the same report to refer to different servers.

commit_list.message:
Basic graphing now supported through cubism.js

* Added graphs model to implement saving graph parameters in the future
* Adding d3/cubism.js and raphael/g.raphael libraries for graphing
* Generating basic cubism.js graph for a given query, styles are wonky

This is super-basic graphing. The one thing I've learned is that
CoffeeScript and d3 don't go well together. d3 and cubism.js use
closures so heavily that the code looks kind of awkward/ugly in
CoffeeScript. Either that or I'm using CoffeeScript incorrectly, which
is entirely possible. =D
